@bulingTang | Auro Wallet  can you please add to Auro Wallet the new API method `signTransaction`?

It is the same as `sendTransaction`, but instead of calling  `await this.postZkTx(signedTx)` it can simply return signedTx, similar to signFields.
The idea is to prepare and sign zkApp tx on web without compiling and proving, and then to send signed tx to cloud prover to be proved and sent to the network.

Update: it is also possible to prove after signing in case the transaction call the method that takes ZkProgram proof as an argument:

```typescript
...
  @method async setValue(value: Field, proof: MyZkProgramProof) {
    proof.verify();
    proof.publicInput.assertEquals(value);
    this.value.set(value);
  }
...
const tx = await Mina.transaction({ sender, fee }, async () => {
      await zkApp.setValue(value, proof);
    });
```
To do so, only the publicInput of the proof need to be calculated before the tx signature, the compiling and proving of ZkProgram can be done later in other worker too.

